kinetic.client

Interface ConnectionListener


  • public interface ConnectionListener
    A ConnectionListener is used to receive asynchronous messages from a connected Kinetic service. Such as unsolicitated status message.

    Upon received an unsolicitated status message, the Java runtime library calls the listener's onMessage if registered.

    Author:
    chiaming

    • Method Detail

      • onMessage

        void onMessage(com.seagate.kinetic.common.lib.KineticMessage message)
        Upon received an unsolicitated status message, the Java runtime library calls the listener if registered.

        The thread execution from the Java client runtime library is serialized such that each sub-sequential messages are delivered only after the previous onMessage call returned.

        Parameters:
        message - the asynchronous message sent from the connected Kinetic service.
